---
import ContentLayout from '@/layouts/content-layout.astro'
---

<ContentLayout
	title="Vocational Dashboard — Ilzam"
	description="Centralized education dashboard for Indonesia's vocational education directorate. REST API, recommender system, and data visualization."
>
	<a href="/work" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">&larr; All work</a>

	<div class="mt-6 flex items-center justify-between">
		<span class="rounded-sm bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium uppercase">Government Tech</span>
		<span class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Indonesia / 2023</span>
	</div>

	<h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-light leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
		Vocational Dashboard
	</h1>
	<p class="mt-2 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
		Centralizing education data for a national directorate.
	</p>

	<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
		{["REST API", "Recommender system", "Data dashboard"].map((tech) => (
			<span class="rounded-full border px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs">{tech}</span>
		))}
	</div>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Challenge</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			Indonesia's vocational education directorate needed a way to centralize data from multiple institutions across the country. Data was scattered across spreadsheets, legacy systems, and manual reports. Decision-makers had no unified view of what was happening across the system.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Approach</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			I built a centralized dashboard that pulls data from multiple sources into a single view. A REST API handles data ingestion and normalization. The frontend provides interactive visualizations for decision-makers. A recommendation engine suggests curriculum adjustments based on industry demand data.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Key Decisions</h2>
		<ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-muted-foreground">
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Data normalization as the first priority.</span>
				Before building any dashboards, the data needed to be clean and consistent. Different institutions used different formats, naming conventions, and reporting periods. Getting this right was the foundation everything else depended on.
			</li>
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Recommendation engine over static reports.</span>
				Static dashboards show what happened. A recommender system helps decide what to do next — suggesting which programs to expand, which to sunset, based on employment outcomes and industry trends.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Result</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			The directorate now has a single source of truth for vocational education data across Indonesia. Decision-makers can see real-time metrics, compare institutional performance, and receive data-driven recommendations for curriculum planning.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-12 border-t pt-8">
		<h3 class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">Related Notes</h3>
		<ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
			<li><a href="/notes/build-vs-buy-early-stage-startup" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">Build vs Buy for Early-Stage Startups</a></li>
			<li><a href="/notes/mvp-stack-choice-2025" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">MVP Stack Choice in 2025</a></li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10 rounded-lg bg-muted/50 p-6 text-center">
		<p class="font-medium">Need a dashboard or data platform built?</p>
		<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
			I've shipped government-scale systems. Let's talk about your project.
		</p>
		<a
			href="https://cal.com/ilzam/intro"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
			class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-foreground px-5 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-background transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
		>
			Book an Intro Call
		</a>
	</section>
</ContentLayout>
